<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: /con and pvp</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tamerlane">Tamerlane</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:07 p.m. 11/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: /con and pvp<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1887" TARGET=_self>/con and pvp</A> (blaczero)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> imagine walking around in that world, you see a fighter in full

<BR>&gt; plate and a glimmering 2h sword... dont you think you would feel
<BR>&gt; that they would be able to wipe your ass up if you were a weak
<BR>&gt; little patchwork'd out lowerlevel character?
<P>&gt; so think about this... if you were actully IN that world walking
<BR>&gt; around, smelling the forest, freezing from walking in the north
<BR>&gt; plains, you could size someone up just by the 'battle scars' and
<BR>&gt; the way the people carried themselves (i.e. more expirenced
<BR>&gt; warriors are more mature, etc...) even if the characters were
<BR>&gt; close in level you would prolly know right away if you could
<BR>&gt; take em out...
<P>&gt; therefore, the /con command is more realistic (helps to add an
<BR>&gt; element that you cannot get with a game) than not because you
<BR>&gt; cant BE in that world to just LOOK at people and see how they
<BR>&gt; carry themselves...
<P>&gt; my opnion.
<BR>I think that the /con command should be a skill. As you gain ability in the skill you get better results from your scan. a first level warrior full of his own abilities should not be able to size up opponents like a 20th level rogue who has made a living out of knowing who to rob and who to leave alone. It should be a skill with race bonuses and bonuses for /con on your race or class and penalties on very different races or classes. a missed skill roll would give you a mistaken reading in that a higher or lower level would be indicated. possibly your skill would go up when you got in a fight with high level mage that you /con'ed as green and got you ass burned off.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
